libbuspirate
------------------------------------------
The libbuspirate is a C library to talk with the bus pirate hardware
(http://dangerousprototypes.com/docs/Bus_Pirate) in raw, binary scripting mode.
The libbuspirate allows to quickly write a short C program to test interfacing
with your favorite hardware.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.3-1
  libbuspirate-devel-0.5.0-1bl1
  libbuspirate0-0.5.0-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.37-2
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-11.2.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-8
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://sourceforge.net/projects/libbuspirate/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/libbuspirate/libbuspirate-0.5.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libbuspirate-0.5.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libbuspirate-0.5.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libbuspirate-0.5.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbuspirate-0.5.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbuspirate0-0.5.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbuspirate-devel-0.5.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libbuspirate)
  /usr/bin/buspirate-demo.exe
  /usr/bin/buspirate-demo24.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libbuspirate.README
  /usr/share/doc/libbuspirate/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libbuspirate/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libbuspirate/README

(libbuspirate0)
  /usr/bin/cygbuspirate-0.dll

(libbuspirate-devel)
  /usr/include/buspirate/buspirate-internal.h
  /usr/include/buspirate/buspirate.h
  /usr/include/buspirate/debug.h
  /usr/include/buspirate/i2c.h
  /usr/include/buspirate/raw.h
  /usr/include/buspirate/spi.h
  /usr/lib/libbuspirate.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libbuspirate.pc

